            <p>HON. MR. SMITH reiterated that it<lb/>was usual to adjourn the House from day<lb/>to day under such circumstances as the<lb/>Government were now placed, but it was<lb/>in the hands of the House to adjourn or<lb/>go on, as they saw fit.<lb/>
